         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0035">
               <p>Andrews was a timber merchant and carpenter in <placeName>Hertford</placeName> who
                  was drawn into the Methodist cause by the preaching of <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers0441.xml"/>Benjamin Colley</persName> in <date
                     when="1766">1766</date>. He soon began holding classes for children in
                     <placeName>Hertford</placeName> and built a school, which became the earliest
                  house used for Methodist worship. While the work in and around
                     <placeName>Hertford</placeName> struggled, Andrews remained a solid supporter
                  until he departed for <placeName>North America</placeName> in <date when="1793"
                     >1793</date>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
